-- Hungary Raises Planned Amount of Debt at Bond Auction as Costs Increase
-- Edith Balazs
-- 2010-06-17T09:32:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-17/hungary-raises-planned-amount-of-debt-at-bond-auction-as-costs-increase.html

          
          
             Hungary raised 50 billion forint
($222 million) in debt today, the planned amount, as borrowing
costs jumped from the previous auction two weeks ago.  
 The government sold 25 billion forint of 2013 bonds at an
average yield of 7.01 percent, up from 6.33 percent on June 3,
according to auction results on the debt management agencyâ€™s
Bloomberg page. It also sold 15 billion forint of 2016 notes at
7.32 percent versus 6.87 percent and 10 billion forint of the
2020 maturity at 7.68 percent compared with 7.38 percent, the
results showed.  
          
          


  


        